# Protei_Bulk CDR (Call Detail Records) Directory

This directory stores all Call Detail Records generated by Protei_Bulk.

## Structure:
- smpp/: CDRs for SMS and SMPP-based campaigns
- http/: CDRs for HTTP API interactions
- internal/: Internal system and control-plane CDRs
- archive/: Rotated and compressed historical CDR data

## CDR Format:
CDRs are stored in CSV format with the following fields:
- Timestamp
- Transaction ID
- Protocol (SMPP, HTTP, etc.)
- Source Address
- Destination Address
- Message Status
- Error Code (if applicable)
- Processing Time
- Additional Metadata

## File Naming Convention:
Format: PROTOCOL_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.cdr
Example: smpp_20250116_143000.cdr

## Rotation:
- CDRs are rotated daily at midnight
- Files older than configured retention period are compressed and moved to archive/
- Compressed format: gzip (.gz)

## Archive:
- Archive files: PROTOCOL_YYYYMMDD.cdr.gz
- Retention period: Configured in config/app.conf
- Old archives can be safely deleted or moved to long-term storage

## Usage:
- Real-time CDR monitoring: tail -f smpp/smpp_*.cdr
- Search CDRs: grep "transaction_id" smpp/*.cdr
- Parse CDRs: Custom scripts in ../scripts/utils/

## Important:
- Do not manually edit CDR files
- Ensure sufficient disk space for CDR storage
- Regular backup recommended for compliance
